Low-frequency contribution to 
and  



The behavior of low-frequency modes is determined by the boundary
conditions and the topological structure of the spacetime. If the
spacetime is asymptotically flat and the characteristic scale of
the gravitational field inhomogeneity  is much less than
the parameter ,
           f /_0  1,
     the low-frequency contributions to  and
 can be expanded in terms of powers
of this small parameter. In the following the zeroth term of this
expansion will be used for approximation of the low-frequency
contributions to  and 
. This means that we choose the long-wave
modes approximately coincident with long-wave modes of the
Minkowski vacuum (in generally accepted terminology this
corresponds to the choice of the Boulware quantum state). For
these modes [
]
